  <div class="main-wrapper">
    <div id="main" class="main">
      
      <div  class=main-content >
        
        
        <div class="body-content">
        
        
          
          
          
          

            
    <p><a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/DonaldTrump" class="body-link" data-vars-item-name="BL-8721341-https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/DonaldTrump" data-vars-event-id="c6">Donald Trump</a> has claimed that, despite his repeated promises that <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/Mexico" class="body-link" data-vars-item-name="BL-8721341-https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/Mexico" data-vars-event-id="c6">Mexico</a> would pay for a <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/border-wall" class="body-link" data-vars-item-name="BL-8721341-https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/border-wall" data-vars-event-id="c6">wall</a> on US southern border, he “obviously never meant Mexico would write a cheque”.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  








  
  
  
  





                
              
            
          

            
    <p>Mr Trump’s website for his 2016 campaign had previously stated that the border country would make a “one-time payment of “$5-$10 billion”.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  



  <div id="mpu0ArticleBody" class="ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--mobile ad-wrapper--mpu0">
  <amp-ad
    height="250"
    width="300"
    class="ad-center"
    type="doubleclick"
    data-slot="/71347885/_main_independent_amp/in_news_amp/in_world_amp/in_americas_amp/in_us_politics_amp/in_us_politics_article_amp"
    json='{
      "targeting":{
        "tile": "mpu0ArticleBody",
        "share": "f936e1d9",
        "gs_channels": ["esi_safe,safe_from_harvey_weinstein,safe_from_emirates_blacklist,pos_animal_cruelty,pos_castrol_blacklist,pos_microsoft_blacklist_microsoft,pos_microsoft_blacklist_wildfire,pos_society_lgbt,pos_terrorism_blacklist,pos_ubs_tax_evasion,safe_from_aegis_blacklist,safe_from_asda,safe_from_collective_landrover,safe_from_emirates_crew_incident,safe_from_facebook_blacklist,safe_from_fas_blacklist,safe_from_halifax_misc_blacklist,safe_from_instagram-mobkoi,safe_from_mobkoi-celine,safe_from_mobkoi_facebook_keyword,gs_politics,shadow9hu7_safe_from_essence_blacklist,gs_politics_american,gs_politics_misc,shadow9hu7_safe_from_workdayh2,shadow9hu7_safe_from_nestle_blacklist,shadow9hu7_safe_from_emirates_pg,shadow9hu7_safe_from_castrol,indy_retirement-conscious_nov16,gv_safe"],
        "docFormat": "amp",
        "article": "8721341,
        "pagetype": "video",
        "topictags": ["donaldtrump,mexico,borderwall"]
      }
    }'
    rtc-config='{"vendors":{"indexexchange":{"SITE_ID":"197232"}},"timeoutMillis":750,"urls":["https://esi.amp.permutive.com/rtc?type=doubleclick"]}'
    data-multi-size="300x250, 300x600"
    data-multi-size-validation="false"
    layout="fixed"
    media="(max-width: 929px)">
  </amp-ad>
</div>







  
  
  
  





                
              
            
          

            
    <p>Instead, the president most recently claimed that Mexico would pay for the wall through changes to trade policy his administration has negotiated to replace the <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/nafta" class="body-link" data-vars-item-name="BL-8721341-https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/nafta" data-vars-event-id="c6">North American Free Trade Agreement</a>. That new deal, the United States-Mexico-Canada Agreement (<a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/usmca" class="body-link" data-vars-item-name="BL-8721341-https://www.independent.co.uk/topic/usmca" data-vars-event-id="c6">USMCA</a>), has not been approved by congress yet but the president said on Thursday that it ”probably will be”.</p>
    

            
              

              
                  
