    <p>The 2016 promise that Mexico would directly pay for the wall was also included in a “pay for the wall” memo Mr Trump’s team issued early that year that proposed pressuring Mexico by cutting off remittances sent from undocumented Mexicans in the United States. It proposed amending the Patriot Act, passed after the 9/11 attacks.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  








  
  
  
  





                
              
            
          

            
    <aside
  class="inline-block inline-related align-left item-count-1 ">
  <h2 class="box-title">Read more</h2>
  
  <ul>
    
    <li>
      <div 
      >
        
        <a href="/news/world/americas/us-politics/prisons-government-shutdown-federal-workers-pay-ms13-gang-terrorists-escape-trump-a8722181.html" data-vars-item-name="related - /news/world/americas/us-politics/prisons-government-shutdown-federal-workers-pay-ms13-gang-terrorists-escape-trump-a8722181.html"
           data-vars-event-id="c29">
          <amp-img src="https://static.independent.co.uk/s3fs-public/thumbnails/image/2019/01/10/17/trump-shutdown-texas.jpg" width="204" height="135" layout="responsive"></amp-img>
        </a>
        
      </div>
      <a href="/news/world/americas/us-politics/prisons-government-shutdown-federal-workers-pay-ms13-gang-terrorists-escape-trump-a8722181.html" data-vars-item-name="related - /news/world/americas/us-politics/prisons-government-shutdown-federal-workers-pay-ms13-gang-terrorists-escape-trump-a8722181.html"
         data-vars-event-id="c29">Prison workers warn of &#39;escapes&#39; as government shutdown continues</a></li>
    
  </ul>
  
</aside>

    

            
          

            
    <p>“It’s an easy decision for Mexico: make a one-time payment of $5-10 billion to ensure that $24 billion [in remittances] continues to flow into their country year after year,” the memo said. “We have the leverage, so Mexico will back down,” it said.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  








  
    <div id="taboola-carousel-thumbnails" class="ad-wrapper ad-wrapper--inline-taboola ad-wrapper--mobile">
  <amp-embed
    width="300"
    height="300"
    type=taboola
    layout=responsive
    data-publisher="eslmedia-theindependent"
    data-mode="alternating-thumbnails-d1"
    data-placement="Carousel Thumbnails"
    data-target_type="mix"
    data-article="auto"
    layout="responsive"
    media="(max-width: 929px)">
  </amp-embed>
</div>

  
  
  
  





                
              
            
          

            
    <p>Speaking outside the White House, the president claimed he “never said they were going to write out a cheque” and that Mexico would pay for it indirectly “many, many times over”.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  








  
  
  
  





                
              
            
          

            
    <p>The president has amended his promise that Mexico would pay for the wall several times over the past couple of years that he has been in office, but his statement on Thursday is one of the first times that he has explicitly denied those earlier promises of direct payment.</p>
    

            
              

              
                
                
                  








  
  
